Former Secretary of State Colin Powell said this week that the FBI has contacted him about his personal email use when he was the nation\'s top diplomat. The contact was part of a review conducted by the State Department inspector general who concluded that Powell and former Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice both received classified information through personal email accounts. The revelation that the State Department believes both Rice and Powell received sensitive information from a personal account could give former secretary Hillary Clinton a new line of defense while she tries to calm the controversy over classified information found on her own private email server.

